        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "How does Ruby's AI differ from a standard answering machine or voicemail?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Ruby doesn't use pre-recorded messages or basic auto-attendants. The AI component works alongside real human receptionists — it handles intelligent routing, captures caller data in real-time, generates detailed call summaries, and learns your preferences over time. Callers always reach a live person, but that person is backed by smart technology that makes every interaction faster and more accurate.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Can I keep my existing business phone number with Ruby?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Absolutely. Ruby works through simple call forwarding — you set your business line to forward to Ruby during hours you choose. Your phone number stays exactly the same. No porting, no new numbers, no confusing transitions. Your customers won't even notice the change, except that someone always answers now.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "h3",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "What happens if a caller needs to reach me urgently?",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "You set the rules. Ruby receptionists follow your specific instructions for every call type. You can designate certain callers, topics, or situations as emergencies that should be forwarded directly to your cell. Everything else gets handled professionally with messages sent to your app or email. You're always in control of what counts as urgent.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
